Summer called, we answered ☀️

We found our dream apartment on @zillow by filtering for outdoor space and a must-have pool—because hosting under the sun was non-negotiable!!!
Now that it’s warm again, we’re bringing out the linens, florals, and citrus for our first alfresco dinner of the season. #ZillowPartner

Woke up at 5AM (yes… on vacation 😭) 

to get in line for Hanauma Bay and it was SO worth it. This place is hands down our favorite snorkel spot on Oʻahu. You do need to plan ahead: reserve online 48 hrs in advance OR show up exactly at 6:45AM for limited walk-in tickets.

We got there early, watched the quick orientation video, and swam with the most colorful fish + turtles in the calmest, clearest water 🐠🐢 VERY Tourist-y but for a good reason.

Other snorkel spots we liked: 
✨Kaimana Beach - in front of Hau Tree
🦀 Shark’s Cove – perf for kids but highly recommend water shoes as it’s suuuper rocky 
🐢 Kaʻena Point – super remote & peaceful
🌊 Hālona Cove – tiny but stunning, near the blowhole
🧘🏽‍♀️ Turtle Bay (Kuilima Cove) – calm & easy if you’re staying up north

Save this for your next Oahu trip ✨
